# Vendored from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/nixon-diamond/nixon-diamond.n3
# Unmodified besides dropping the trailing `log:impliesAnswer` query line
# (this engine has no query/goal-extraction mechanism -- see main.rs, this
# suite only ever runs full materialize() and checks derived facts).
#
# This is a *rule-priority* example -- Rule 2 (Republicans are NonPacifist)
# must be fully evaluated before Rule 1 (Quakers are Pacifist, guarded by
# `log:notIncludes { ?x a ex:NonPacifist }`) so the SNAF guard can see the
# NonPacifist fact and block Rule 1. Closed two ways, both in `datalog.rs`/
# `reasoner.rs`:
# 1. `datalog::validate_rules`'s stratification analysis now looks *inside*
#    a `log:notIncludes` literal's quoted-formula argument (the same way
#    `collect_formula_vars` already did for `log:implies`) and adds a
#    genuine negative dependency edge on whatever relation that inner
#    pattern names -- here, Rule 1 (deriving ex:Pacifist) is forced into a
#    stratum strictly greater than Rule 2 (deriving ex:NonPacifist), so
#    Rule 2's stratum runs to a full fixpoint before Rule 1's stratum
#    starts at all.
# 2. `Reasoner::materialize`'s fixpoint also now applies each rule's
#    derivations to the live `TripleIndex` immediately (in declaration
#    order) rather than batching until the whole iteration finishes, so
#    even within one stratum/iteration a later rule can observe an
#    earlier rule's same-iteration output.
# Only `ex:NonPacifist` is derived, matching upstream EYE.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#> .
@prefix ex:  <http://example.org/nixon#> .

ex:RichardNixon  a ex:Quaker, ex:Republican .

{ ?x a ex:Quaker .
  ?SCOPE log:notIncludes { ?x a ex:NonPacifist } .
}  =>  { ?x a ex:Pacifist } .

{ ?x a ex:Republican }  =>  { ?x a ex:NonPacifist } .
